[2] New York and New Jersey
Date: Sun 4 Nov 2018
Source: The Yeshiva World [abridged, edited]
https://www.theyeshivaworld.com/news/general/1616501/measles-outbreak-updates-anti-vaxxers-to-defy-ban-and-send-kids-to-school-lakewood-giving-hundreds-of-vaccines-as-parents-panic.html


YWN [The Yeshiva World] has been reporting extensively about the measles outbreak, currently spreading through multiple Chareidi [Orthodox Jewish] communities due to the so-called "anti-vaxxer" cult, who refuse to give the highly recommended and effective vaccine. Health departments are extremely concerned, and there is panic spreading among parents of children in schools.

The outbreak has spread from Israel, where over 1200 people have been sickened, and an unvaccinated 18-month-old child [died].

Below are the latest updates:
Rockland county (Monsey, Spring Valley, New Square)
---------------------------------------------------
As of this report, there are close to 50 cases in Rockland county. 2 children have been hospitalized -- one in intensive care -- because of the measles outbreak, and the health department is taking more precautions to make sure it doesn't spread among students.

The Viznitz Monsey Girls School announced that any child who is not immunized, can't return to school for 21 days. No "religious exemption" is accepted. A religious exemption does not work when there is a measles outbreak.

Rockland county's Commissioner of Health, Dr Patricia Schnabel Ruppert, announced [Wed 31 Oct 2018] that all schools in the Village of New Square are now required to keep students who are un-vaccinated or under-vaccinated against the disease home until 21 days have passed since the last case of measles is confirmed in the county.

However, YWN has obtained a recording taken on Sunday morning [4 Nov 2018] from one of the anti-vaxxer hotlines in Rockland county. A woman giving an update to the listeners says that "it's ok to send your children to school tomorrow, Monday morning [5 Nov 2018] in Monsey -- even without a letter. We will be distributing/getting a letter out as soon as possible."

At least 2 Shuls [synagogues] that YWN knows of have informed their members that anyone not vaccinated can not enter the Shul.

This follows the story YWN published on [Fri 2 Nov 2018], where at least 6 Shuls in Lakewood have made the same rule. 6 schools in Lakewood have made the same rule, and others are expected to follow suite.

New Jersey (Ocean county, Lakewood)
----------------------------------
Hundreds of people are showing up at their pediatricians to get vaccinations, following the report of at least 4 confirmed cases of measles in Lakewood.

The Ocean County Health Department and the NJ EMS [New Jersey Emergency Medical Services] Task Force have arrived in Lakewood, and set up large tents outside CHEMED [Center for Health Education, Medicine, & Dentistry] Health Clinic, and have ordered approximately 1500 vaccinations to be administered to those requesting it.

At Doctor Shanik's office, the premier and senior pediatrician in Lakewood, there are reportedly no vaccines available as they have run out.

New York City (Williamsburg, Boro Park)
---------------------------------------
In NYC, the Health Department is reporting 11 new cases of children with confirmed measles, bringing the total to 17. Chassidish [Orthodox Jewish] communities in Williamsburg and Borough Park are affected. The children with measles range in age from 7 months-4 years.

