[7] Colombia (Cesar department)
Date: Thu 1 Nov 20181:40 PM COT
Source: RCN Radio [in Spanish, machine trans., edited]
https://www.rcnradio.com/colombia/caribe/autoridades-confirman-caso-de-sarampion-en-valledupar


Authorities have confirmed the 1st case of measles registered in Valledupar. The secretary of Departmental Health, Nicolas Mohrez Muvdi, assured that it is an imported case that was registered in a 25-year-old young man, who was in a family integration in the corregimiento San Jose de Oriente, municipality of La Paz.

It was there where he had contact with a Venezuelan person who had the disease and who is presumed returned to his/her country.

Mohrez Muvdi explained that, "After several days, the young man presented the symptoms and went to a health center in the city of Valledupar, which immediately informed the health authorities about the suspected case."

On the other hand, the official stressed that the Valledupar case becomes the most recent case in the department [Cesar], "after 2 cases were confirmed in the municipality of Codazzi."

Among the measures carried out by the authorities is the vaccination strategy carried out in Valledupar, as explained by the local Health Secretary, Elba Yolanda Ustariz Martinez, who pointed out that "you have to be alert to the symptoms, such as high fever with rash, conjunctivitis, malaise, lack of appetite and nasal secretions."

Ustariz Martinez also recalled that the infection is transmitted from one person to another through droplets of saliva ejected by the patient when speaking or sneezing, "hence the importance of using masks, washing hands frequently, keeping the house ventilated, and, in the presence of those symptoms, not self-medicating but consulting a doctor immediately.

In the construction of the so-called shock plan, the authorities highlighted the active participation of the Eduardo Arredondo Daza Hospital as reinforcement was immediately initiated to expand vaccination coverage.

Both the departmental and municipal health secretaries emphasize the importance of applying the complete vaccination scheme. That is why they reiterate the call to parents to go to the nearest hospital. "We remind you that they are 2 doses of viral triple, at the 1st year of life and at 5 years."

In addition to this, because of the outbreak situation, the Ministry of Health orders that a double viral dose be given to the entire population between 6 months of age and 49 years of age; regardless of their nationality.

[Byline: Pepe Moron]

